Bola Bamigbola, Osogbo A 53-year-old businessman, Abdul-Azeez Bello, was on Friday remanded in a correctional facility by an Osun State Magistratesâ€™ Court sitting in Osogbo for defrauding one Mary Ajani of the sum of N2m. Bello was arraigned on two counts of obtaining under false pretences and fraud. The accused, who promised to link Ajani with a company dealing in planks sometime in 2017, was said to have been paid the sum of N2m by the victim. Bello was said to have failed to supply the items. The offences were said to be contrary to and punishable under sections 419, 383 and 390 (9) of the Criminal Code, Cap 34 Vol. 2, Laws of Osun State of Nigeria, 2002. When the charges were read to him, the accused pleaded not guilty. Counsel for the accused, Tolulope Ayodele, applied for his bail and the prosecutor, Oladiran Ayodele, did not oppose the application. But Magistrate Olusegun Ayilara did not grant the request. He ordered that the accused be remanded in the Ilesa Correctional Centre and adjourned the matter till October 18, 2019, for ruling on the bail application. Copyright PUNCH.
